                          July 19 (Bloomberg) -- Amanda McCluskey, head of sustainability and responsible investment at Colonial First State Global Asset Management, talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about Australia's Aug. 21 election, and its implications for the government's policy on climate change and investors.
     A plan to tackle climate change will be released during the election campaign and the commitment to reconsider carbon-trading plans at the end of 2012 still stands, Gillard told Australian Broadcasting Corp. radio today.(Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
